RACE.RACE_TEXT: Ontario Derby - Grade3 WOODBINE RACE 9 1 1/8M All Weather Track CR: 104. Stakes Purse 150000. FOR THREE-YEAR-OLDS.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SOLO ALBUM took command up front into the first turn, dictated the pace down the backside, repelled the early challengers pressing the issue three eighths from the wire, opened up when asked in upper stretch and had something in reserve to comfortably hold off any rivals at the finish. TOUCH'N RIDE tracked in the third flight outside early on, edged closer to the frontrunners through the backstretch, started a rally between horses into the far turn, had to be throttled down momentarily at the three furlong pole, recovered quickly to bid three wide at the quarter pole but was not match against the winner driving to the wire. COOL KISS was in the third flight on the inside in the beginning, started to make a run between runners into the final turn, had to check briefly in midturn, regrouped to be in the mix four wide turning for home and finished up strongly to garner third money at the finish. TWOWAYCROSSING hopped on the break to trail, was allowed to find his stride down the backstretch still unhurried, began to pick up runners reaching for more ground three wide outside on the far turn, swung out in the six path to be in range of the leaders turning for home and rallied down the stretch on the wrong lead for a minor share in the end. TWIN CITY was steadied on the rail entering the first turn, had a good position nestled behind the front foursome at the half, nudged on the fence keeping pace on the far turn and finished up evenly on the rail down the lane. FOREVER DIXIE stalked on the outside close to the back of the pack in the early going, made a brief run four wide around foes three eighths from the line but could not find more and yielded between horses at the quarter pole. STANLEY HOUSE was off slowly on the break, settled near the back into the first turn, made an early move four deep advancing outside down the backstretch, dueled three wide for the lead three furlongs from the finish, could not sustain the run turning for home and tired at the furlong pole. AMERICAN BLAZE stalked near the rear on the rail, co-trailed on the inside down the backstretch, was roused three eights from home but was losing ground to rivals and had little to show in the stretch drive. VELOCITOR tracked the duo in the first turn, prompted the pace on the outside down the back straight, came under a hard ride trying to maintain position up front battling between horses three furlongs out and gave way at the quarter pole. RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 11 5F All Weather Track CR: 93. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 36500. INNER TURF FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $5,000 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $10,000. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Since August 21 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since T hen Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (Races Where Entered For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered For Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ALICIA'S KID pressed the pace on the rail in the beginning, spurted clear on the fence from three other rivals midway around the bend, opened up in upper stretch and cruised home unchallenged for the victory. TOMCAT BLACK settled in midfield between horses at the half, waited patiently looking for a seam two furlongs from the finish, surged up the fence at the eighth pole and won the battle for place nearing the wire. NEOPHYTE was tucked in the rail behind the front pack down the backside, inched closer when coaxed on the fence midpoint on the turn, rallied up the fence in upper stretch and was outgamed late for the second money. MASTER SPY was under a snug hold watching the foursome three furlongs from the wire, lacked running room behind the leaders at the quarter pole, swung outside for a clear run in the six path at the furlong marker and was gaining late but could do no better than a minor share at the finish. TRICKY MAGICIAN was void of early speed to settle near the rear, started to rally four wide at the quarter marker, swung out with run in the seven path at the top of the lane and finished up willingly outside horses down the stretch. CHANCEL forced the pace three wide between rivals, could not go on the winner midway on the turn, fought on gamely with runners on either side until the eighth pole and tired in the final sixteenth. GRAND ALLIANCE stalked at the back in the early stages, offered a brief run three wide on the outside three eighths from the line and could not be a presence driving to the finish. CRAFTY CONQUEST had a slim advantage in the two path on the outside down the back straight, was relegated to chasing the winner a quarter mile from home, could not find more in the lane and faltered with a furlong to go. COMMANDER TOM tracked behind the engaging four leaders with a half remaining, had little to offer on the turn, backed through the field with five sixteenths from the wire and emptied out at the top of the stretch. SHAKOO MAKOO was in the mix up front outside four deep at the half,, continued to chase outside at the quarter pole and stopped in deep stretch. EXECUTIVE SIGHT was bumped soundly on the break, trailed down the backside, stalked at the back on the rail on the turn and lacked a rally on the fence to the finish line.
